216 - Combination Sum III
Problem Statement

Find all valid combinations of k numbers that add up to n such that:

Only numbers from 1 to 9 are used.
Each number can be used at most once.
Return all possible unique combinations.
Approach: Backtracking

We generate combinations using numbers from 1 to 9.

At each step:

Choose a number and add it to the current combination.
Reduce the remaining target.
Move to the next number since a number cannot be reused.
Backtrack by removing the last chosen number and explore other possibilities.

A combination is valid only when:

The remaining target becomes 0.
Exactly k numbers have been selected.
Algorithm
Start from number 1.
Recursively try numbers from the current position to 9.
Add the chosen number to the current combination.
Reduce the target by the chosen number.
If target == 0 and current.size() == k, store the combination.
Stop recursion if:
target < 0
current.size() > k
Backtrack by removing the last added number.
Continue exploring remaining choices.
Code
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> combinationSum3(int k, int n) {
        List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();
        backtrack(1, k, n, new ArrayList<>(), result);
        return result;
    }

    private void backtrack(int start, int k, int target,
                           List<Integer> current,
                           List<List<Integer>> result) {

        if (target == 0 && current.size() == k) {
            result.add(new ArrayList<>(current));
            return;
        }

        if (target < 0 || current.size() > k) {
            return;
        }

        for (int i = start; i <= 9; i++) {

            current.add(i);

            backtrack(i + 1,
                      k,
                      target - i,
                      current,
                      result);

            current.remove(current.size() - 1);
        }
    }
}
